Using Microsoft Authenticator

Using Microsoft Authenticator on Your Mobile Device


1. When you log into Office 365, you will need to set up 2FA for your Microsoft account. You can do this manually here too


5. Select "Mobile App", "Receive Notifications", then click "Set Up" until you reach the screen with a QR code


6. Download the Microsoft Authenticator app on your mobile device


7. Select to add a "Work or school account", then select "Scan QR code" and scan the QR code you were provided


8. After you have scanned the QR code, click "Next"



9. You will receive a push notification on your device, approve this notification to complete the setup of 2FA for Office 365


10. Last step is to add your mobile phone number as a backup recovery method

Refer here for help Exporting a 2FA Token when moving to a new device
